## Overlays

**Extends Component**

Controls the elements that get rendered over the main app, so dialogs/modals etc

### render

Component's Renderable JSX

Returns **any** 

## Overview

**Extends Component**

Overview Page, The main page

### formatDiff

Formats the Difficulty to 3 decimal points

#### Parameters

-   `diff` **any** 

Returns **[Number][439]** Diff but with 3 decimal point places

### componentDidMount

Component Mount Callback

### reDrawEverything

Set by {NetworkGlobe}, ReDraws all Pillars and Archs

### componentWillUnmount

Component Unmount Callback

### componentDidUpdate

Component Prop Update Callback

#### Parameters

-   `prevProps` **any** 

Returns **any** 

### fetchDifficulty

Get the Difficulty from the network

### setupcontextmenu

Sets up the context menu

#### Parameters

-   `e` **any** 

### blockDate

Returns the Block Date of the last given block

Returns **any** 

### connectionsIcon

Returns the Connections icon based on how many connections the user has

Returns **any** 

### trustIcon

Returns the trust icon

Returns **any** 

### blockWeightIcon

Returns the block weight icon

Returns **any**

Returns if the Globe should be rendered

Returns **any** 

### numberWithCommas

#### Parameters

-   `x` **any** 

Returns **any**

-   `stat`

## Globe

**Extends Component**

The 3D Globe on the overview page.

### componentDidMount

Mounting event from React, used to start the globe up

### contextRestoredHandler

### contextLostHandler

Handle Webgl Context Lost Event

#### Parameters

-   `event` **any** 

### componentDidUpdate

Update event from React

#### Parameters

-   `prevProps` **any** 

### componentWillUnmount

Unmount event from React

### pointRegister

Register point/pillar on the globe

Returns **any** 

### addSelfPoint

Add globe to the renderer

### removeAllPoints

Remove all points on the globe

### destroyPoint

Remove point/pillar from the globe

#### Parameters

-   `deadPoint` **any** Point to remove

### arcRegister

Register a arc with the globe

### animateArcs

Animate all the Curves on the globe

### destroyArc

Removes the unused Curve

#### Parameters

-   `deadCurve` **any** Curve to remove

### onWindowResize

Event when the window resizes

### stop

Stop the animation

### start

Start the animation

### animate

Animate the globe

### renderScene

Renders the screen to the THREE's canvas

Component's Renderable JSX

Returns **JSX** JSX

## Curve

Object for the Curves on the globe

### getSplineFromCoords

Creates a spline from one point to the next

#### Parameters

-   `pointOne` **any** Contains {lat and lng}
-   `pointTwo` **any** Contains {lat and lng}

Returns **THREE.CubicBezierCurve3** 

### clamp

Clamp a number between min and max

#### Parameters

-   `num` **[Number][439]** Input Value
-   `min` **[Number][439]** Min Value
-   `max` **[Number][439]** Max Value

Returns **[Number][439]** Return Value

### coordinateToPosition

Translates a Lat and Lng to a Vector3 on a sphere

#### Parameters

-   `lat` **[Number][439]** Latitude
-   `lng` **[Number][439]** longitude
-   `radius` **[Number][439]** radius of sphere

Returns **THREE.Vector3** Point on sphere

### play

Play the Animation

### stop

Stop the animation

### restart

Restart the animation

## Transactions

**Extends Component**

Transactions Page

### componentDidMount

Component Mount Callback

### componentDidUpdate

Component Updated Props Callback

#### Parameters

-   `previousprops` **any** 

Returns **any** 

### componentWillUnmount

Component Unmount Callback

### setConfirmationsCallback

The callback for when we want to update just the confirmations

#### Parameters

-   `incomingData` **any** The data provided by the daemon to be used to update the confirmations

### setOnmountTransactionsCallback

The callback for the on Mount State

#### Parameters

-   `incomingData` **any** the data provided by the daemon to be used to update the chart

### updateChartAndTableDimensions

Updates the height and width of the chart and table when you resize the window

#### Parameters

-   `event` **any** The event hook for changing the window dimentions

Returns **any** can return null if chart is udefined

### openTxDetailsModal

Open Tx Detail modal

### transactioncontextfunction

This is the method that is called when the user pressed the right click

#### Parameters

-   `e` **any** event hook for html for right click

### copysomethingtotheclipboard

Copy to Clipboard

#### Parameters

-   `instringtocopy` **any** The string to copy to the clipboard

### getTransactionData

Gets all the data from each account held by the wallet

#### Parameters

-   `finishingCallback` **any** The Method to use after all the data is processed from the daemon

Returns **null** Cen return null if no data is retreived, exit for this method is finishingCallback

### transactionTimeframeChange

Set the display property in state from the dropdown element

#### Parameters

-   `value` **any** The Value of the selected item in the dropdown menu

### DownloadCSV

Download CSV

### gatherAllFeeData

Gather All fee data for every debit/send transaction

### setCSVEvents

Set events for the CSV Listener

#### Parameters

-   `events` **any** 

### updateProgress

Each time a transaction is done processing, run this.

### finishCSVProcessing

When proccessing is finished, open up the save dialog

### saveCSV

creates a CSV file then prompts the user to save that file

#### Parameters

-   `DataToSave` **\[any]** Transactions to save

### transactiontypefiltercallback

#### Parameters

-   `categoryFilter`  

### transactionamountfiltercallback

#### Parameters

-   `e`  

### transactionaddressfiltercallback

Callback for when you change the address filter

#### Parameters

-   `e`  

### filterByCategory

Filter the transactions based on the CategoryFilter

#### Parameters

-   `inTransactions` **\[any]** Current list of transactions to filter

Returns **\[any]** List of transactions after the filtering

### filterbyAmount

Filter the transactions based on the AmountFilter

#### Parameters

-   `inTransactions` **\[any]** Current list of transactions to filter

Returns **\[any]** List of transactions after the filtering

### filterByAddress

Filter the transactions based on the AddressFilter

#### Parameters

-   `inTransactions` **\[any]** Current list of transactions to filter

Returns **\[any]** List of transactions after the filtering

### filterByTime

Filter the transactions based on the DisplayTimeFrame

#### Parameters

-   `inTransactions` **\[any]** Current list of transactions to filter

Returns **\[any]** List of transactions after the filtering

### returnAllFilters

Returns all the transaction that have been filtered by the filter

#### Parameters

## styled

Important note - This file is imported into module_preload.js, either directly or
indirectly, and will be a part of the preload script for modules, therefore:

-   Be picky with importing stuffs into this file, especially for big
    files and libraries. The bigger the preload scripts get, the slower the modules
    will load.
-   Don't assign anything to `global` variable because it will be passed
    into modules' execution environment.
-   Make sure this note also presents in other files which are imported here.
